    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_17_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_17",
      "description": "Available is a 2008 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) featuring the legendary 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. This M97 powerplant delivers a broad torque curve and immediate throttle response, mated to a precise G97 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis dynamics are defined by a classic rear-engine layout, providing exceptional longitudinal traction and communicative hydraulic-assisted steering. Maintenance is up to date, including a documented IMS bearing inspection and RMS replacement, ensuring the mechanical integrity of the drivetrain. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing McPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for superior lateral stability. Braking is handled by four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors, exhibiting zero fade and firm modulation. This is a driver-focused example with a strong mechanical foundation, ideal for those who prioritize analog feedback and engineering excellence.",
